Two opposite and outstretched testes, the anterior one to the left of the intestine, and the posterior one to the right. Spicules paired, slender and arcuate, 79–88 μm long and 4.0–4.4 anal body diameter. Gubernaculum complex, paired large parts slender and proximally pointed, 20–24 μm long; paired small parts stout, distally hook-shaped, pointed in the proximal end, with a ventral apophysis in the middle part, 8–11 μm long. No precloacal supplements (
Figure 2D
).
